{"id":"1705.00201","submitter":"Murray Daw","authors":"Hengjia Wang, Doyl Dickel, and Murray S. Daw","title":"Theoretical treatment of anharmonicity of vibrational modes of\n  single-walled carbon nanotubes","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mes-hall","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We report a computational study, using the \"moments method\" [Y. Gao and M.\nDaw, Modelling Simul. Mater. Sci. Eng. 23 045002 (2015)], of the anharmonicity\nof the vibrational modes of single-walled carbon nanotubes. We find that modes\nwith displacements largely within the wall are more anharmonic than modes with\ndominantly radial character, except for a set of modes that are related to the\nradial breathing mode which are the most anharmonic of all. We also find that\nperiodicity of the calculation along the tube length does not strongly affect\nthe anharmonicity of the modes, but that the tubes with larger diameter show\nmore anharmonicity. Comparison is made with available experiments and other\ncalculations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 29 Apr 2017 15:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-02"}
